function countDifferentSubsequenceGCDs(nums) {
    let maximum = Math.max(...nums);
    let gcdCount = new Array(maximum + 1).fill(0);

    for (const num of nums) {
        for (let i = 1; i * i <= num; i++) {
            if (num % i === 0) {
                gcdCount[i]++;
                if (i * i !== num) {
                    gcdCount[num / i]++;
                }
            }
        }
    }

    let differentGCDs = 0;
    for (let i = 1; i <= maximum; i++) {
        if (gcdCount[i] > 0) {
            differentGCDs++;
        }
    }

    return differentGCDs;
}
```

    1. First, find the maximum number of the given array.
2. Create an array `gcdCount` with the length of (maximum + 1), initializing all the values to 0.
3. Iterate through `nums`. For each number, find its divisors and increment the count of the divisors in the `gcdCount` array.
4. Iterate through the `gcdCount` array starting from index 1 to `maximum`, and count the number of non-zero values.
5. Return the count of non-zero values as the number of different GCDs.

